 Critics Association Awards 2011|19 December 2011]]\n| [[Chicago Film Critics Association Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" | <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.indiewire.com/2011/12/the-tree-of-life-leads-chicago-critics-awards-50467/ |title=\u2018The Tree of Life\u2019 Leads Chicago Critics Awards |last=Knegt |first=Peter |date=19 December 2011 |accessdate=6 August 2016 |work=[[IndieWire]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160818105104/http://www.indiewire.com/2011/12/the-tree-of-life-leads-chicago-critics-awards-50467/ |archive-date=18 August 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | [[David di Donatello Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"1\" | 2011\n| [[David di Donatello for Best Foreign Film|Best Foreign Film]]\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" | <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.yahoo.com/tv/italys-davide-di-donatello-nominations-announced-104509488.html |title=Italy's Davide di Donatello Nominations Announced |last= |first= |date=7 April 2011 |access-date=6 August 2016 |work=[[Yahoo!]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160910232451/https://www.yahoo.com/tv/italys-davide-di-donatello-nominations-announced-104509488.html |archive-date=10 September 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" rowspan=10| [[Genie Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"10\" | [[31st Genie Awards|10 March 2011]]\n| [[Academy of Canadian Cinema and Television Award for Best Motion Picture|Best Motion Picture]]\n| [[Luc D\u00e9ry]] and [[Kim McCraw]]\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"10\" | <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/arts/incendies-barney-s-version-dominate-genies-1.1078773 |title=Incendies, Barney's Version dominate Genies |date=10 March 2011 |accessdate=6 August 2016 |work=[[CBC News]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815093108/http://www.cbc.ca/news/arts/incendies-barney-s-version-dominate-genies-1.1078773 |archivedate=15 August 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Academy of Canadian Cinema and Television Award for Best Achievement in Direction|Best Direction]]\n| Denis Villeneuve\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Academy of Canadian Cinema and Television Award for Best Performance by an Actress in a Leading Role|Best Actress]]\n| [[Lubna Azabal]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Academy of Canadian Cinema and Television Award for Best Screenplay|Best Adapted Screenplay]]\n| Denis Villeneuve\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Academy of Canadian Cinema and Television Award for Best Achievement in Art Direction/Production Design|Best Art Direction]]\n| [[Andr\u00e9-Line Beauparlant]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Academy of Canadian Cinema and Television Award for Best Achievement in Cinematography|Best Cinematography]]\n| [[Andr\u00e9 Turpin]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Academy of Canadian Cinema and Television Award for Best Achievement in Editing|Best Editing]]\n| [[Monique Dartonne]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Academy of Canadian Cinema and Television Award for Best Achievement in Overall Sound|Best Sound]]\n|  [[Jean Umansky]] and [[Jean-Pierre Laforce]]\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Academy of Canadian Cinema and Television Award for Best Achievement in Sound Editing|Best Sound Editing]]\n|  [[Sylvain Bellemare]], Simon Meilleur and Claire Pochon\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Make-Up\n|  Katryn Casault\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" | [[International Film Festival Rotterdam]]\n| 2011\n| UPC Audience Award\n| Denis Villeneuve\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmfestivals.com/blog/international_film_festival_rotterdam/incendies_is_rotterdam_2011_audiences_favourite_340000_visits_to_anniversary_edition|title=Incendies is Rotterdam 2011 audiences\u2019 favourite; 340,000 visits to anniversary edition|date=6 February 2011|access-date=1 August 2016|website=Filmfestivals.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160910144323/http://www.filmfestivals.com/blog/international_film_festival_rotterdam/incendies_is_rotterdam_2011_audiences_favourite_340000_visits_to_anniversary_edition|archive-date=10 September 2016|url-st