tan commentaries |date=1988 |publisher=State University of New York Press |isbn=9780887065897 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=v5-0LLlNNTEC&newbks=1&newbks_redir=0&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false}}\n* {{Citation|last1=Lopez |first1=Donald S. |title=The Lotus S\u016btra : a biography |date=2016 |publisher=Princeton University Press |isbn=978-0-691-15220-2}}\n* {{Citation|url=http://www.buddhanet.net/pdf_file/buddha-teachingsurw6.pdf|title=The Buddha and His Teachings|last=Mahathera|first=Naranda|publisher=Buddha Dharma Education Association Inc|year=1998|isbn=|location=Taiwan|pages=|access-date=26 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180826174309/http://www.buddhanet.net/pdf_file/buddha-teachingsurw6.pdf|archive-date=26 August 2018|url-status=live}}\n* {{Citation|last1=Malalasekera|first1=G.P.|title=Dictionary of P\u0101li proper names|url=http://www.palikanon.com/english/pali_names/sa/saariputta.htm|volume=2|year=1937|edition=1st Indian|location=Delhi|publisher=[[Motilal Banarsidass Publishers]]|isbn=81-208-3022-9|author-link=G P Malalasekera}}\n* {{Citation|url=https://books.google.com/?id=8Au_lIP1ZnQC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Dictionary of P\u0101li Proper Names: N-H|last=Malalasekera|first=Gunapala Piyasena|publisher=Motilal Banarsidass Publishe|year=2007|isbn=978-81-208-3022-6|location=|pages=|language=en}}\n* {{Citation|last1=Migot|first1=Andr\u00e9|title=Un grand disciple du Buddha: S\u0101riputra. Son r\u00f4le dans l'histoire du bouddhisme et dans le d\u00e9veloppement de l'Abhidharma|date=1954|url=http://www.persee.fr/docAsPDF/befeo_0336-1519_1954_num_46_2_5607.pdf|journal=Bulletin de l'\u00c9cole fran\u00e7aise d'Extr\u00eame-Orient |volume=46|issue=2|trans-title=A great disciple of the Buddha: S\u0101riputra, his role in Buddhist history and in the development of Abhidharma|language=fr|doi=10.3406/befeo.1954.5607|author-link=Andr\u00e9 Migot}}\n* {{Citation|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0TMsdV8lS8wC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Buddhist Saints in India: A Study in Buddhist Values and Orientations|last=Ray|first=Reginald A.|date=1994|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-535061-6|location=|pages=|language=en}}\n* {{Citation|url=https://www.wisdomlib.org/buddhism/book/the-great-chronicle-of-buddhas/d/doc364489.html|title=The story of Upatissa (S\u0101riputta) and Kolita (Mah\u0101 Moggall\u0101na) [Part 1]|last=Sayadaw|first=Ven. Mingun|year=1990|website=www.wisdomlib.org|access-date=2020-01-17}}\n* {{Citation|last1=Shaw|first1=Sarah|title=Character, Disposition, and the Qualities of the ''Arahats'' as a Means of Communicating Buddhist Philosophy in the ''Suttas''|date=2013|url=http://www.ahandfulofleaves.org/documents/A%20Companion%20to%20Buddhist%20Philosophy_Emmanuel.pdf|encyclopedia=A companion to Buddhist philosophy|editor1-last=Emmanuel|editor1-first=Steven M.|edition=first|location=Chichester, West Sussex|publisher=[[Wiley-Blackwell]]|isbn=978-0-470-65877-2}}\n* {{Citation|url=http://www.ahandfulofleaves.org/documents/Buddhist%20Meditation%20An%20anthology%20from%20the%20Pali%20canon_Sarah%20Shaw.pdf|title=Buddhist meditation : an anthology of texts from the P\u0101li canon|last=Shaw|first=Sarah|date=2006|publisher=Routledge|isbn=0-203-00731-X|location=London|pages=|oclc=70199246}}\n* {{Citation|title=Brill's encyclopedia of Buddhism Vol Two|last=Silk|first=Jonathan A.|publisher=|others=Hin\u00fcber, Oskar von,, Eltschinger, Vincent,, Bowring, Richard, 1947-, Radich, Michael|year=2019|isbn=978-90-04-29937-5|location=Leiden|pages=|oclc=909251257}}\n* {{Citation|url=https://books.google.com/?id=MH4EAAAAYAAJ|title=Buddha and Buddhist synods in India and abroad|last=Thakur|first=Amarnath|date=1996|publisher=Abhinav Publications|isbn=|location=|pages=|language=en|access-date=2019-10-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215114437/https://books.google.com/books?id=MH4EAAAAYAAJ&hl=en|archive-date=2019-12-15|url-status=live}}\n* {{Citation|last=Thomas|first=Edward J.|title=The History of Buddhist Thought|url=https://archive.org/download/historyofbuddhis031559mbp/historyofbuddhis031559mbp.pdf|year=1953|series=History of Civilization|edition=2nd|location=London|publisher=[[Routledge and Kegan Paul]]|author-link=Edward J. Thomas}}\n* {{Citation|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Pw0q_iD3ZrAC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Untying the Knots in Buddhism: Selected Essays|last=Wayman|first=Alex|date=1997|publisher=Motilal Banarsidass Publ.|isbn=978-81-208-1321-2|location=|pages=|language=en}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Sariputta}}\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Wiktionary}}\n\n* [http://buddhism.2be.net/The_Buddha's_Chief_Disciples The Buddha's Chief Disciples]* [http://buddhism.2be.net/The_Buddha's_Chief_Disciples The Buddha's Chief Disciples]\n* [http://what-buddha-said.net/library/DPPN/sa/saariputta.htm S\u0101riputta]\n* [http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20051001132642/http://accesstoinsight.org/lib/bps/wheels/wheel090.html The Life of \u015a\u0101riputra - compiled and translated from P\u0101li by Nyanaponika Thera]\n* [http://www.budsas.org/ebud/rdbud/rdbud-02a.htm GREAT MALE DISCIPLES - Part A Upatissa (Sariputta) and Kolita (Moggallana)] by Radhika Abeysekera\n* [http://www.niu.edu/burma/publications/jbs/vol4/Abstract4_DaultonOpt.pdf Jack Daulton, \"Sariputta and Moggallana in the Golden Land: The Relics of the Buddha's Chief Disciples at the Kaba Aye Pagoda\"]\n*[http://www.peacebeyondsuffering.org/new-talks.html,    Ajahn Achalo Bhikkhu \"Around Rajgir \u2013 Sariputta the Great Disciple\"]\n{{Buddhism topics}}\n{{Gautama Buddha}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Foremost disciples]]\n[[Category:Arhats]]\n[[Category:Converts to Buddhism]]\n[[Category:5th century BC in religion]]\n", "name_user": "Vami IV", "label": "safe", "comment": "ditto", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C5%9A%C4%81riputra"}
